<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_EP20_AdventureAwaits_SettingUpGetaways" s="484092">
  <T n="category">481599<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_Category_AdventureAwaits--></T>
  <T n="name">0x40607D9E<!--String: "Setting Up a Getaway"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_SettingUpGetaways_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:e7c7221877929123</T>
      <T n="text">0x2A49F382<!--String: "Getaways are a new way to send your Sims off on a fully planned event, whether it's a romantic retreat, a skill-building camp, or a wild social experiment. Unlike standard event types, Getaways come with roles to play, activities to follow, and rewards to earn. Open the calendar to <font color="#199C2C"><b>Add Getaway</b></font> or open the phone travel app and select <font color="#199C2C"><b>Plan a Getaway</b></font>!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_SettingUpGetaways_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:e7c7221877929120</T>
      <T n="text">0x9C737B04<!--String: "First off, choose where and when your Getaway will happen! In the Locations tab, select any eligible lot from the list: Custom Venues, Residential Lots, Residential Lots of Unknown Sims, and many more are available to choose from.\n\nThen select the <font color="#199C2C"><b>Start and End Time</b></font> of the Getaway, and set the <font color="#199C2C"><b>duration</b></font>. You can plan anything from a few hours to multiple days. Want this Getaway to repeat weekly on the calendar? Select the <font color="#199C2C"><b>Recurring Weekly</b></font> checkbox and choose which days it should repeat on the calendar. For example, if you select Fridays and Mondays, the Getaway will automatically reschedule for the next Friday and Monday once the current Getaway ends."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_SettingUpGetaways_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:e7c7221877929121</T>
      <T n="text">0xA52D98BF<!--String: "After setting the location and time for your Getaway, the next step is deciding which <font color="#199C2C"><b>Roles</b></font> will be part of it. In the Roles section, you'll view two tabs: <font color="#199C2C"><b>Current Roles</b></font> and <font color="#199C2C"><b>Role Library</b></font>.\n\nCurrent Roles lists all the roles included in this specific Getaway. This is where you assign Sims, customize outfits, set default behaviors, and define role criteria!\n\nTo add a new role to your Getaway, select <font color="#199C2C"><b>Create Role</b></font>. Once you've customized a role, you can save it to the Role Library to reuse later. The Role Library is a shared collection of saved roles. If you want to use a role from the Library, you can import it into Current Roles at any time. This makes it easy to build a library of your favorite setups and quickly drop them into future Getaways!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_SettingUpGetaways_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:e7c7221877929126</T>
      <T n="text">0xDF66BF65<!--String: "Each role listed in Current Roles can be customized to shape how Sims behave during the Getaway. Make sure your household Sim is assigned to the role you want them to take part in. To assign a specific Sim or household Sim to a role, start by selecting the role's Sim portrait in the Current Roles panel. Then, in the Role Properties panel, select the Sim portrait again to open up the Sim picker.\n\nKeep in mind for non household Sims attending the Getaway, you don't have to assign them to specific roles. For any unassigned roles, we'll help fill in Sims who match the Role criteria and <font color="#199C2C"><b>Total Sim Count</b></font> you've set.\n\nAs an advanced setting, you can also define a set of default role activities and customize each role's outfit, ensuring every Sim matches the tone of the getaway or role they are in!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_SettingUpGetaways_5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:e7c7221877929127</T>
      <T n="text">0x81D931FA<!--String: "Once you've set up the roles, it's time to customize the schedule for your Getaway!\n\nStart by selecting <font color="#199C2C"><b>Add Timeslot</b></font>, then choose when that timeslot begins. Each timeslot must be at least three hours long. And each timeslots end time is defined by the next timeslots start time. You can add as many timeslots as you'd like to structure the flow of the day."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_SettingUpGetaways_6.png">2f7d0004:00000000:e7c7221877929124</T>
      <T n="text">0x592D699C<!--String: "For each timeslot, you'll assign activities to every role by selecting them from the dropdown. This is where you define the <font color="#199C2C"><b>Role Activities</b></font> of what each role will be doing during that window of time whether that's eating outdoors, kayaking around, socializing, or stirring up a bit of mischief.\n\nThe <font color="#199C2C"><b>Main Activity</b></font> represents the central focus of the timeslot. It's the shared moment that all Sims are expected to engage with, acting as the anchor for that part of the schedule. However, Sims will always prioritize their assigned Role Activity over the Main Activity, so if you want a Sim to lead or drive a key moment, be sure that activity is set under their Role Activity."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_SettingUpGetaways_7.png">2f7d0004:00000000:e7c7221877929125</T>
      <T n="text">0xD7AAFE9F<!--String: "You can save the preset, either as a new template or by overriding an existing one anytime in the Getaway planner. Presets include both the roles and the full schedule and can be reused in future Getaways or even attached to Custom Venues for quicker setup later!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_SettingUpGetaways_8.png">2f7d0004:00000000:e7c722187792912a</T>
      <T n="text">0x2C072126<!--String: "Getaway also has a <font color="#199C2C"><b>cost</b></font> or an <font color="#199C2C"><b>earning</b></font>! Depending on where you host it, your household can either spend or earn Simoleons.\n\nIf you choose to host a Getaway at your own residential lot, your household will earn Simoleons based on the number of Sims participating. Think of it like charging an admission to an exclusive Getaway, and your household Sim becomes the host of the event. On the other hand, hosting a Getaway on any other lot, whether it's a park, gym, or Custom Venue, it will cost Simoleons. Larger, fancier venues with more participants will naturally cost more during the stay of the Getaway.\n\nThe full cost (or profit) is shown before finalizing your Getaway, so you can always tweak your plans to fit your household funds."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP20\UI\Lessons\EP20_SettingUpGetaways_9.png">2f7d0004:00000000:e7c722187792912b</T>
      <T n="text">0xAD7BBC0A<!--String: "Getaway <font color="#199C2C"><b>Rules</b></font> are where the fun really kicks in! This is where you customize the structure, stakes, and twists of your Getaway. At the core of this system is <font color="#199C2C"><b>Elimination</b></font>. If you choose to enable it, you can decide how Sims are eliminated and what criteria they're judged on.\n\nOnly one elimination rule can be active at a time, and you can choose between two types: <font color="#199C2C"><b>Lowest Score Loses</b></font> and <font color="#199C2C"><b>Lowest Progress Loses</b></font>. Lowest Score Loses judges based on the current status Sims arrive with at the Getaway. For example, if you choose Creativity Elimination, the Sim with the lowest Creativity Skill upon arrival will be eliminated. On the other hand, Lowest Progress Loses is all about how much a Sim improves during their time at the Getaway. So even Sims with low Creativity Skill still stand a chance to become the final winner!"--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
